-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Nov 6
-- 
-- Thu Nov 06, 2014 02:45AM EST
-- None



SOFIA, Nov 6 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Bulgarian President Rosen Plevneliev has given biggest party GERB a mandate to form a government. Boiko Borisov, the leader of the centre-right GERB, announced he will either have a cabinet ready or return the mandate within 24 hours (Presa, Standart, Trud, 24 Chasa, Monitor). -- Centre-left ABV will study options for joining a coalition government of GERB and the Reformist Bloc if those two political forces accept ABV's proposals, Ivailo Kalfin, chairman of the party's parliamentary group, said (Standart, Trud, Presa). -- Bulgaria's central bank will announce its decision about the faith of the troubled Corporate Commercial Bank (Corpbank) until Tuesday, sources familiar with the issue, said (24 Chasa, Presa). -- Bulgaria's state security agency seized 40 kg heroin in a joint operation with the interior ministry in the southern town of Plovdiv (24 Chasa, Trud). -- Four foreign citizens have been taken to hospital following a brawl that involved Syrian and Afghan nationals in a refugee camp in the southern town of Harmanli (Standart, Monitor).